FBIS4-61964 "drsov091_f_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-091 Daily Report 10 May 1994 National Affairs Rukh Leader To Head New Centrist Bloc in Parliament Rukh Leader To Head New Centrist Bloc in Parliament LD1005190894 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 1600 GMT 10 May 94 LD1005190894 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service Ukrainian BFN [Text] The new composition of deputies of Ukraine's Supreme Council will begin its work on 11 May. An agreement on creating a parliamentary centrist bloc was approved at a meeting of leaders of several deputies' groups and factions. This was stated by Vyacheslav Chornovil, head of the Rukh group in the Supreme Council, at a news conference in Kiev on 10 May. He noted that representatives of the "Tsentr" [Center] group, the Rukh group, "Derzhavnist" [Statehood], and "Za Reformy Dlya Narodu" [in Support of Reforms for the People] had joined the bloc. Chornovil stressed that a meeting of the bloc will discuss the groups' positions on basic issues, which are to be submitted for parliament's consideration.
